Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Infectious salmon anemia (ISA) is a disease of Atlantic salmon (_Salmo salar_) caused by an orthomyxovirus, which affects mainly fish maintained in marine water or exposed to the sea. The disease can be systemic and lethal, characterized by severe anemia and hemorrhages in several organs.

It is a disease of great economic impact for the salmon industry. The disease is of obligatory notification to the OIE. - Mod.PMB

Maps of Norway can be seen at http://www.questconnect.org/images/map_of_norway.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4742438,57469. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ`

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4742438,57469.]
